The court blocked a decision regarding the NYPD's search and seizure policy.
A federal appeals court on Thursday blocked a judge's decision to require changes to the New York Police Department's surveillance and search program and dismissed her from the case.
The United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit held that Judge Shira Scheindlin's decision was adjourned pending the outcome of the city's appeal.
The judge ruled in August that the city had violated the Constitution by implementing its program to monitor and interrogate citizens.
