The Court of Appeal held that the judge should be dismissed from the case because she had violated the Code of Conduct for Judges by compromising the need for a judge to avoid any appearance of bias, in part because of a series of media interviews and public statements in which she publicly responded to criticism of the court.
The judge ruled that police officers were violating the civil rights of tens of thousands of people by wrongfully targeting black and Hispanic men as part of their surveillance and search program.
