Bamford was sentenced to 15 days in a low-security detention center on the outskirts of Phuket rather than a women's prison.
She is the daughter of former Australian rugby league player Peter Tunks, who appealed to the Canberra Foreign Office to help his daughter.
Tunks told the Sydney Sunday Telegraph that the whole family was  extremely concerned  about her daughter's well-being and wanted her to return to Australia.
 We obviously had a stressful time, but we hope to get her home safely as soon as possible, said Tunks.
Bamford appealed the verdict and was released on bail of 50,000 baht.
In Australia, the press reported that she was on holiday in the Krabi region of southern Thailand.
